args: We've handed the perpetrator off\nto the town guard. Well done, all.
Now to meet back up with Akasha\nand track down that vampire.
Knowing her, Akasha will have predicted\nall of this and taken action accordingly.
Her research may already have turned up\nsomething useful. Let's hurry back to her.
Yeah, before things get ugly.\nEr, well, ugliER, I guess.
Nnngh... This is...inside the castle?\nNo, not the Halidom.
I trust you slept well, my beautiful guest?
No, the word ＂guest＂ does you disservice,\nfor tonight, you are my bride!
Ah, I see. This is your illusion, then;\na castle within a dream.
Is it not to your liking? But say the word,\nand I will provide any backdrop you desire.
Well? What would you ask of me?
My, what a lovely bit of spellcraft.\nIt is EVER so fascinating...
Is that so? Then perhaps you will cede\nyour body unto me and make an offering\nof your blood.
Believe me, a far more delicious dream\nawaits you on the other side.
And might that dream be the glamour\nyour kind casts upon their prey when\nthey dine on human blood?
I've read how no greater pleasure exists.\nRather a shame that all who taste it lose\ntheir lives in the process.
Your beauty is matched only by your wits.\nTruly, you are a prime specimen!

To merely take your blood would be a
crime without measure. No, you must
share MY blood—and my unending life
along with it!

The very thing countless humans have
sought for in vain. Eternal life—eternal
BEAUTY! Have you truly never hungered
for such?
Ah, forgive me. I'm simply tickled to meet\na vampire who is so very...VAMPIRE-Y.
Why, I'm fit to burst with joy!
To think I would make your acquaintance\non this of all nights...
I couldn't ask for a more perfect fit for\nHalloween, that time of strange costumes,\nsong and dance, and tricks or treats.
Oh yes. You will be the perfect sacrifice.
You...you are not human.\nBut then, what ARE you?
What am I indeed! Oh, I know:\nLet's make a riddle of the answer.
What do you THINK I am?\nGo on, now...
S-stay back! This dream is a world of MY\ncreation, and if anything happens to me,\nyour consciousness will share my fate!
Oh, that's VERY sweet—but you needn't\nworry your pretty head about me, dear.
Now, I know you vampires enjoy the dark,\nso I think I have just the spot...
Ah, yes. Here we are! A fitting prison\nto hold my lovely new sacrifice.
My illusion...shattered? But how?!\nHow is this POSSIBLE?!
Hush, dear. No cause for fear.\nTonight is Halloween, so let's enjoy\nthe evening together, you and I.
Oh dear. It looks like someone\ndidn't bring any candy with them.
In that case, I don't suppose you can\ncomplain when you get tricked, mmm?
No no no no no NO NO NOOOOO!
Answer if you can hear us!
I fear the vampire took me by surprise.
Hold on. I'll break down the door!
Perfectly fine, thank you. When I fought\nback, the vampire turned tail and fled back\nto his own world.
Wait, so you chased a vampire out of\nthis entire material plane by YOURSELF?!
Indeed I did. I'm quite strong, you know.
Though I am very glad to see you safe,\nI wish you had not been so reckless.
Me too. But with the vampire gone and\nthe man who summoned him arrested,\nI suppose we can put this behind us.
Yes, that would seem to\nresolve the matter.
Well, chasing a vampire off sounds like\npretty tiring work, so let's get back to the\nHalidom and let you rest.
Did you not...hear that? Just now?
My ears must be crammed full of candy\nor something, because I could swear...
It has been a long day of running about for\nall of us, so what say I bring some leftover\ncookies along as a post-dinner treat?
*gasp* *pant* C-can anyone hear me?!\nHelp! Get me out of here!
Where IS this place? There's nothing here!\nNothing...anywhere...
